    "(4) The fourth lesson, and a corollary of the third, is that the way an agent solves a problem ultimately depends on its resources, broadly construed.",
    "Besides time and memory-size, these resources include heuristics (efficient strategies), cognition (capacities for perceiving and acting in the world), 10 knowledge, and learning.",
    "In reality, you might mix aspects of Ψ and Φ.",
    "You might select a few key ingredients as a basis that you already know yields a reasonably tasty salad, and imagine whether this basis could benefit from further additions.",
